Function Reference/get delete post link « WordPress Codex
-----------

Returns URL to move a post to the trash as string value.

Can be used within the WordPress loop or outside of it. Can be used with
pages, posts, attachments, and revisions.

Usage
-----

`  <?php echo get_delete_post_link( $id ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The post ID
    Default: *None*

 `deprecated` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Not used.
    Default:

 `force_delete` 
:   ([*bool*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Bool "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to bypass trash and force deletion.
    Default: false

Return Value
------------

 (string) 
:   A string containing the permalink.

Changelog
---------

-   Since: 2.9.0

Source File
-----------

`get_delete_post_link()` is located in `wp-includes/link-template.php`

